It means:
â€œLook at the event (which Iâ€™m calling $process) and filter where the principal user is SYSTEM.â€
Here $process is simply a nickname youâ€™ve given for an event pattern that involves process activity.
ðŸ§± 2. Why People Use $process, $login, $file, etc.
Because you can have multiple event types in the same rule â€” each representing a different action or stage of an attack.
For example:
events:
  $login.metadata.event_type = "LOGIN"
  $process.metadata.event_type = "PROCESS_LAUNCH"
Now in your condition: section, you can relate them:
